🔴 **Tool Issue** — `RuleArmTemplate` uses `any` for multiple properties

```ts
export interface RuleArmTemplate {
    contentVersion: string;
    parameters: any;      // ← any
    resources: any[];     // ← any[]
    schema: string;
    variables: any;       // ← any
}
```

`parameters`, `resources`, and `variables` are all typed as `any` / `any[]`. These represent structured ARM template data and should ideally be typed as `Record<string, unknown>` and `Record<string, unknown>[]` respectively. The current typing allows arbitrary values to be passed without compile-time checks.

**Fix:** Please report this in the [generation tool repository](https://github.com/Azure/autorest.typescript/issues) so the emitter can produce stronger types for `RuleArmTemplate` properties.
